<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="wchar_t" id="wchar_t">wchar_t</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
The keyword wchar_t is used to declare wide character variables. wchar_t size is implementation dependent, therefore development of portable applications cannot assume that popular character representation, such as <a href="http://www.unicode.org/" class="urlextern" title="http://www.unicode.org/"  rel="nofollow">Unicode</a>, can fit into a wchar_t on every platform and using any compiler.
</p>

<p>
Also see the <a href="../data_types" class="wikilink1" title="data_types">data types</a> page.
</p>

